# Cursor Rules for Amigos Exatec Project

## Project Context
This is a React + Vite frontend application for Tec de Monterrey Alumni Association, deployed to Hostinger.

## Hostinger MCP Configuration
The Hostinger MCP server is configured in Cursor settings (not in this file).
API Token: Configured in Cursor user settings under `mcpServers.hostinger-mcp.env.API_TOKEN`

## Important Notes
- Never commit API tokens or sensitive credentials to version control
- The MCP server configuration is stored in Cursor's user settings, not in project files
- See HOSTINGER_MCP_SETUP.md for setup instructions

## Deployment
- Frontend builds to `frontend/dist/`
- Deploy using GitHub Actions (configured) or Hostinger MCP
- See HOSTINGER_DEPLOYMENT.md for details

